article.headline: Temple cruises past East Carolina 66-53
article.story: PHILADELPHIA -- Will Cummings scored 17 points and Temple cruised to a 66-53 victory over East Carolina on Saturday afternoon. Cummings was a perfect 7 of 7 from the line and had six assists. Jesse Morgan added 14 points, Josh Brown chipped in 10, and Jaylen Bond finished with 16 boards for Temple (19-7, 10-3), which holds third place in the American Athletic Conference. The Owls closed out the first half on a 10-1 run to lead 34-18 at the break, and East Carolina could get no closer than 11 points in the second half. A three-point play from Brown and a pair of free throws from Cummings gave Temple an 18-point advantage with 5:46 to play. The Owls didn't score in the final 4:20, but just five points from East Carolina wasn't enough to close the deficit. Terry Whisnant scored 13 points for the Pirates (11-14, 4-8).
